                <note rend="inline" type="source">833.00/671: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-31T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 31, 1940—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>46. Your 88, May 30, 10 a.m. Please keep the Department closely informed by
                    telegram of any developments.</p>
                <p>By order of the President the heavy cruiser <hi rend="italic">Quincy</hi> now off
                    Guantanamo has been instructed to proceed immediately to Rio de Janeiro and from
                    there directly to Montevideo for “friendly visits of courtesy”. You will be
                    informed subsequently by telegram of the date of arrival.</p>
                <p>I think it would be well for you to consider, possibly in consultation with the
                    appropriate members of the government, any special arrangements which could be
                    made to give significance to the call of the <hi rend="italic">Quincy.</hi>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
